{"metadata":{"symbolKind":"protocol","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib13MutexProtocolP","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"MutexProtocol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MutexProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MutexProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Protocol"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MutexProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"text":"PointerWrapper","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Take for example the following function:","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}]},{"code":["  int","  give_me_next_number (void)","  {","    static int current_number = 0;","","    \/\/ now do a very complicated calculation to calculate the new","    \/\/ number, this might for example be a random number generator","    current_number = calc_next_number (current_number);","","    return current_number;","  }"],"syntax":"C","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is easy to see that this won’t work in a multi-threaded"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"application. There current_number must be protected against shared"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"access. A ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used as a solution to this problem:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"C","code":["  int","  give_me_next_number (void)","  {","    static GMutex mutex;","    static int current_number = 0;","    int ret_val;","","    g_mutex_lock (&mutex);","    ret_val = current_number = calc_next_number (current_number);","    g_mutex_unlock (&mutex);","","    return ret_val;","  }"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Notice that the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is not initialised to any particular value.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Its placement in static storage ensures that it will be initialised","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to all-zeros, which is appropriate.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is placed in other contexts (eg: embedded in a struct)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"then it must be explicitly initialised using "},{"code":"g_mutex_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" should only be accessed via g_mutex_ functions."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol","isActive":true},{"text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMutex"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For a con